or=Plagwitz%2CL&author=Varghese%2CJ)\n17. Sandmann, S. et al. Benchmark evaluation of DeepSeek large language models in clinical decision-making. *Nat. Med.* **31**, 2546–2549 (2025).\n18. Chen, J. et al. CoD, Towards an Interpretable Medical Agent using Chain of Diagnosis. In Findings of the Association for Computational Linguistics: ACL 2025 (ed. Che, W. et al.), 14345–14368 (Association for Computational Linguistics, Vienna, Austria, 2025).\n19. Liévin, V., Hother, C. E., Motzfeldt, A. G. & Winther, O. Can large language models reason about medical questions? *Patterns* **5**, 100943 (2024).\n20. Zuo, Y. et al. MedXpertQA: Benchmarking Expert-Level Medical Reasoning and Understanding. In Forty-second International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML 2025).\n21. Tordjman, M. et al. Comparative benchmarking of the DeepSeek large language model on medical tasks and clinical reasoning. *Nat. Med.* **31**, 2550–2555 (2025).\n22. Zhao, Z., Jin, Q., Chen, F., Peng, T. & Yu, S. A large-scale dataset of patient summaries for retrieval-based clinical decision support systems. *Sci. Data* **10**, 909 (2023).\n    [Article](https://doi.org/10.1038%2Fs41597-023-02814-8) \n    [PubMed](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&db=PubMed&dopt=Abstract&list_uids=38110415) \n    [PubMed Central](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10728216) \n    [Google Scholar](http://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?&title=A%20large-scale%20dataset%20of%20patient%20summaries%20for%20retrieval-based%20clinical%20decision%20support%20systems&journal=Sci.%20Data&doi=10.1038%2Fs41597-023-02814-8&volume=10&publication_year=2023&author=Zhao%2CZ&author=Jin%2CQ&author=Chen%2CF&author=Peng%2CT&author=Yu%2CS)\n23. Wu, C. et al. Towards generalist foundation model for radiology by leveraging web-scale 2D&3D medical data. *Nat Commun* **16**, 7866 (2025).\n24. National Library of Medicine. PMC open access subset. <https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/tools/openftlist/> (2003).\n25. Wein